xplhan is a small program to allow an RS-485 home automation network (HAN) to bebridged on to an xPL home automation backbone. This program is a companion to the HAN daemon located at http://github.com/hwstar/hand.

It can be run as a daemon, or in the foreground. There are command line options
to select the com port, log file, debug level, and broadcast interface. For a complete list of command line options, type ./xplhan --help once the program is built.

To compile xplhan, compile and install xPLLib on your system first.

